Description: Body sherd of North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos or krater; interior reserved; exterior: two lions, with added red, facing across large rosettes; thick fill of blobs; part of band below.
Curator's comments: Joins 1924,1201.1021, and from same vase as 1924,1201.987 and 1017.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.609)
